DataElement.preferredDefinition: Data about data; information that describes another set of data.:A non-proprietary, third generation modelling language. The Unified Modeling Language is an open method used to specify, visualise, construct and document the artifacts of an object-oriented software-intensive system under development. The UML represents a compilation of "best engineering practices" which have proven successful in modelling large, complex systems.:A grouping of things based on shared common attributes._The words or language units by which a thing is known._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
